AB We describe our experience of developing scientific software in an
   ongoing multidisciplinary research project participated by information
   scientists and astronomers. In particular, we reflect on how the
   interdisciplinary collaboration is facilitated by the development of a
   unique boundary object - a hybrid map of the Universe and scientific
   discoveries. With reference to theories of interdisciplinary
   communication, we underline that information Visualization serves a
   fundamental role in scientific software development. The impact of
   information visualization can go far beyond the content representation,
   and can facilitate communications across distinct disciplines.
