ID MASS EXTINCTIONS
AB In ibis article, we describe a generic approach for tracking and
   visualising the structure of a knowledge domain based on author
   co-citation and co-citation patterns derived from citation databases.
   The goal is to summarise and synthesis latent structures of knowledge
   domains as reflected through scientific literature available on the
   Internet, in a wide range of digital libraries, and publishers' online
   outlets. We extend our work in visualising to a broader subject domain,
   namely the mass extinctions. The domain of the mass extinctions is
   visualised base on a citation analysis of articles appeared in the Web
   of Science. We illustrate how the integrated approach such as factor
   analysis and pathfinder network scaling are used to capture the
   research front of a knowledge domain. We discuss the results
   corroborate with our earlier work.
