AB Information visualisation has become a truly wide-ranging
   interdisciplinary endeavor. Researchers, practitioners, and end users
   are embracing the vibrant field from a variety of distinct but
   interrelated perspectives. As the field becomes increasingly diverse,
   one must address a number of fundamental questions. What exactly is
   information visualisation about? Where does it come from? Where is it
   going? This article highlights some of the most salient perspectives to
